    e_answer_describe: "<p>tan A =&nbsp;<span class="math-tex">\(\frac PB\)</span> =&nbsp;<span class="math-tex">\(\frac43\)</span>&nbsp;(given)</p>
    
    <p><img alt="" src="https://dk7h1f5gq849l.cloudfront.net/photos/questions/2022-01-11-131114-3-Windows-Photo-Viewer-1641887027-f884a89b-63b6-47e1-94e4-f02041db6c7d.png" style="height:148px; width:139px" /></p>
    
    <p>by using Pythagoras</p>
    
    <p><span class="math-tex">\(\Rightarrow\)</span>&nbsp;<span class="math-tex">\(H^2\)</span>&nbsp;=&nbsp;<span class="math-tex">\(P^2+B^2\)</span></p>
    
    <p><span class="math-tex">\(H^2\)</span>&nbsp;=&nbsp;<span class="math-tex">\(4^2+3^2\)</span></p>
    
    <p><span class="math-tex">\(H^2\)</span>&nbsp;= 25</p>
    
    <p>H = 5</p>
    
    <p><span class="math-tex">\(\Rightarrow\)</span>&nbsp;Now, sin A =&nbsp;<span class="math-tex">\(\frac PH\)</span>&nbsp;=&nbsp;<span class="math-tex">\(\frac45\)</span>.</p>",
